These code for protins in signalling and antigens in Salmonella. Many of them are also in E. coli, which could be because of horizontal gene transfer between prokaryotes. They are both bacteria and could thus exchange genes. Furthermore, E. Coli and Salmonella could very well be homologous (they could easily share a common ancestor).
